Commentary: Junaid Khan to Azhar Ali, 2 runs, superb start from Azhar, lunges forward to drill an elegant drive through the covers for a couple
Junaid Khan to Azhar Ali, 1 leg bye, too straight from Junaid. On the leg stump and Azhar gets a bit of pad on that, towards the keeper. A leg bye

Junaid Khan to Gayle, OUT, gone. Gayle fails again. Junaid gets him again. What a big blow this is. Full delivery on middle and leg, a bit of movement. Gayle doesn't get close enough to the pitch and is caught with leaden-feet in his crease. The umpire raises the finger and Gayle slowly trudges off
Wicket: ['CH Gayle lbw b Junaid Khan 0 (1b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00']

Commentary: Junaid Khan to Delport, FOUR, supreme shot from Delport. Full outside off, too full and Delport leans into an exquisite drive past wide mid-off for four
Junaid Khan to Delport, no run, fullish length on off at 135 kph. Delport defends to mid-off
Junaid Khan to Delport, no run, nice end from Junaid. Length on off, all Delport can do is stride forward and block
Tait to Azhar Ali, no run, nice start from Tait. Good length on off, Azhar stays forward and blocks
Tait to Azhar Ali, no run, massive appeal from Tait. Hustles Azhar for pace and strikes him in front of leg as he falls over while playing the stroke. Sliding down leg, easy decision
Tait to Azhar Ali, no run, overly full on off and middle, driven to mid-on
Tait to Azhar Ali, 1 run, too straight and flicked into the gap at midwicket for a run
Tait to Delport, no run, beautiful lines. A bit of away movement on off, Delport stays in his crease to push to mid-off
Tait to Delport, no run, driven towards cover
Junaid Khan to Azhar Ali, no run, good delivery from Junaid. Fullish on off and solidly blocked by Azhar
Junaid Khan to Azhar Ali, FOUR, smashed. Good batting from Azhar, putting the pressure back on Junaid. Shimmies down and heaves the ball over mid-on
Junaid Khan to Azhar Ali, 1 run, length on off, Azhar guides a dab to third man. Played that late.
Junaid Khan to Delport, 2 runs, great timing from Delport. Another shimmy to the pitch to flick over midwicket for a couple. Coming hard at Junaid here
Junaid Khan to Delport, no run, yorker on off, defended into the surface
Junaid Khan to Delport, no run, lovely bowling. Slower ball outside off, Delport is beaten all ends up as he comes down again to try and slog. Comprehensively beaten
Tait to Azhar Ali, 1 run, back of a length on off, Azhar gets high on his toes to steer towards third man

Tait to Delport, 2 runs, squeezes the drive in the gap at extra cover. Overly full on off, Delport is hustled a bit for pace but goes through with a drive. Somehow, the ball goes past extra cover for a couple
Tait to Delport, 1 run, good length on off, top-of-off stuff. Guided to third man

Tait to Azhar Ali, FOUR, just using the pace is Azhar. Displaying quality batsmanship. Waits for Tait to provide him with a poor delivery and he nudges this one off his hips past short fine leg for four
Tait to Azhar Ali, no run, fullish length on off, defended
Tait to Azhar Ali, no run, overpitched on off. Azhar drives back to Tait
Wahab Riaz to Delport, no run, almost hits the off stump. Fuller length with just enough inswing to sneak through bat and pad
Wahab Riaz to Delport, no run, blocked from the crease to mid-off
Wahab Riaz to Delport, 1 run, slower ball on off, Delport comes down again and badly times his drive to long-on
Wahab Riaz to Azhar Ali, no run, worked off his pads to midwicket
Wahab Riaz to Azhar Ali, 1 run, back of a length on middle, Azhar feigns a big heave but nurdled to deep square leg instead
Wahab Riaz to Delport, no run, thick inside edge onto the pad. Nice delivery, banged in on a good length outside off. A bit of away swing as well
Mohammad Asghar to Azhar Ali, no run, Asghar starts with a shortish delivery outside off, chopped into the off side with a cut
Mohammad Asghar to Azhar Ali, 1 run, not much turn. Slides on with the arm on middle and leg, Azhar flicks to deep midwicket for a run
Mohammad Asghar to Delport, 1 run, too short, too straight. Punched down to long-on
Mohammad Asghar to Azhar Ali, 1 run, bowled from wider of the crease, skids on to middle but Azhar's flick diverts the ball to midwicket
Mohammad Asghar to Delport, SIX, big hit. Very big. Delport gets down and slog sweeps it easily over the midwicket boundary. A bit too full. Delport takes full toll
Mohammad Asghar to Delport, no run, jabbed into the covers off the full delivery
Sammy to Azhar Ali, 1 run, offcutter to start outside off, worked down to long-on
Sammy to Delport, 1 run, another offcutter. This is short and wide, Delport executes his premeditated slap to long-on
Sammy to Azhar Ali, 1 run, nudged off his pads to deep midwicket
Sammy to Delport, 1 run, too straight and clipped to midwicket off his pads
Sammy to Azhar Ali, no run, shortish length outside off, Azhar plays a cross-batted heave that goes to cover. Lost all his shape
Sammy to Azhar Ali, FOUR, better batting. Short and wide, begging to be hit and Azhar obliges with a flayed cut past point. Whistles to the fence
Mohammad Asghar to Delport, no run, fired in on off, Delport stays back and blocks
Mohammad Asghar to Delport, 1 run, poor ball. Not great batting either. Very far down leg, Delport reaches for it to flick to backward square leg. Free run is not accepted
Mohammad Asghar to Azhar Ali, 1 run, tapped towards the bowler for a quick single. That is an impressive run
Mohammad Asghar to Delport, 1 run, shortish and wide, stabbed away towards point with a cut
Mohammad Asghar to Azhar Ali, 1 run, overly full on off, worked to deep midwicket. Hafeez prevents the second
Mohammad Asghar to Delport, 1 run, turned off his pads to short fine leg to end a tidy over from Asghar
Sammy to Delport, no run, slower offcutter on off, driven to cover
Sammy to Delport, 1 run, short and wide outside off, a jab finds cover.
Sammy to Azhar Ali, 1 run, hit deep into the midwicket region. The fielder runs in, collects and fires back a quick throw to prevent the second
Sammy to Delport, 1 run, another offcutter on off, pushed to long-on

Sammy to Azhar Ali, OUT, the lack of boundaries has resulted in Azhar throwing his wicket away. Slower offcutter again on leg, Azhar backs away and slogs one deep in the air, long-on settles under it for an easy take
Sammy to Delport, 1 run, drilled to long-off
Wicket: ['Azhar Ali c Tamim Iqbal b Sammy 25 (26b 3x4 0x6) SR: 96.15']

Commentary: Shahid Afridi to Delport, 1 run, legbreak on leg to start, clipped with the spin to deep midwicket
Shahid Afridi to Umar Akmal, 1 run, flat on middle, Akmal presses forward to drive to long-on. Good feet movement
Shahid Afridi to Delport, no run, another nudged to midwicket. Akmal sends his partner back
Shahid Afridi to Delport, 1 run, turned away to midwicket again. This time, they get one
Shahid Afridi to Umar Akmal, 1 run, nicely played. Too short and wide from Afridi. Cut towards short third man
Shahid Afridi to Delport, 1 run, flat on middle and leg, worked to deep square leg
Sammy to Delport, FOUR, finally, the batsmen get a poor delivery and Delport lays into this. Short on middle and leg, Delport helps it along its way to the backward square leg boundary
Sammy to Delport, 1 run, punched off the back foot to long-off
Sammy to Umar Akmal, 1 run, offcutter on off, clipped to deep midwicket
Sammy to Delport, 1 run, another offcutter. Clever bowling from Sammy. Pushed to long-on.
Sammy to Umar Akmal, 1 run, a bit short outside off, steered to third man
Sammy to Delport, no run, another offcutter outside off, pushed tamely to cover. Great stuff from Sammy
Shahid Afridi to Umar Akmal, FOUR, great shot that is. Gets width outside off, and Akmal cuts late into the gap between point and short third man. Finds the gap beautifully
Shahid Afridi to Umar Akmal, 1 run, hit into the gap, to the sweeper cover
Shahid Afridi to Delport, 1 run, shortish delivery on leg, Delport goes deep in his crease to flick to midwicket

Shahid Afridi to Umar Akmal, 2 runs, just wide of a diving Sammy. Tossed up outside off, a bit of turn but Akmal goes for a lofted drive with the spin. Take the outside half of the bat and lobs towards point. Just evades him eventually
Shahid Afridi to Umar Akmal, 1 run, clipped off his pads for another run to deep midwicket
Shahid Afridi to Delport, 1 run, offspinner or the googly. Delport goes deep in his crease and picks the variation to work to deep midwicket
Wahab Riaz to Delport, no run, 111 kph, slower delivery from the returning Wahab, pushed to cover from the crease

Wahab Riaz to Delport, FOUR, too wide outside off to pull but Delport goes through with the stroke, a thick inside edge takes a bit of glove from the keeper but still makes its way to the fine leg fence
Wahab Riaz to Delport, FOUR, discernibly poor delivery that. On the pads and Delport tickles it past short fine leg and to the backward square leg boundary
Wahab Riaz to Delport, 1 run, good stuff from Delport. Pushes this to long-on
Wahab Riaz to Umar Akmal, 2 runs, nudged off his pads to fine leg for a couple. Found a sizeable gap at backward square leg
Wahab Riaz to Umar Akmal, FOUR, gone through mid-off. Very poor from Junaid. Fullish outside off and driven to mid-off. Junaid over runs it and allows it through. Three extra runs gifted
Tait to Delport, 1 run, back of a length on off, pushed to long-on
Tait to Umar Akmal, 1 run, shortish but not too wide. Wide enough for Akmal to cut to sweeper cover
Tait to Delport, 1 run, great running. Tucked to midwicket for a quick run and set off immediately. No hesitation
Tait to Umar Akmal, 1 run, short and wide, Akmal uses the pace to steer to third man. 100 up
Tait to Delport, no run, lovely change in length. Bangs it in on middle and Delport is forced to duck underneath
Tait to Delport, no run, slower ball outside off, wonderful end to a great over. Yorker and Delport is beaten
Mohammad Asghar to Umar Akmal, no run, short and wide to start after the break, a hint of turn. Chopped to extra cover
Mohammad Asghar to Umar Akmal, 1 run, flat on off, worked to deep midwicket
Mohammad Asghar to Delport, FOUR, too short and Delport rockets a pull to the midwicket boundary to get to his fifty. Splendid innings this so far
Mohammad Asghar to Delport, 1 run, flat and wide outside off, scythed away to the sweeper cover
Mohammad Asghar to Umar Akmal, 1 run, slower outside off, a bit of spin as well. Akmal goes back and works it to deep midwicket against the spin

Mohammad Asghar to Delport, SIX, awful delivery and Asghar is duly punished. Short down leg, ample time for Delport to pick it, go deep in his crease and thrash the pull over the backward square leg boundary.
Junaid Khan to Umar Akmal, 2 runs, wristily flicked to deep square leg. From around the wicket, full and straight
Junaid Khan to Umar Akmal, 2 runs, great fielding from Wahab at the third man boundary. Shortish delivery, Akmal goes for a pull but gets a thick outside edge which flies towards third man
Junaid Khan to Umar Akmal, 1 run, big slog from Akmal, loses his shape but gets an inside edge onto his pad for a run
Junaid Khan to Delport, no run, full toss outside off, it seemed like Delport was beaten by the surprise of the speed of the delivery
Junaid Khan to Delport, 1 run, yorker on off, driven past cover. Delport looks for two, but won't get it
Junaid Khan to Umar Akmal, 1 run, another full toss outside off, drilled down to long-on by Akmal
Wahab Riaz to Umar Akmal, FOUR, sliced over point. Good shot selection that. Gets width on a full delivery and Akmal throws the bat at it to get it over point for four

Wahab Riaz to Umar Akmal, FOUR, great effort from long-off, but that goes through Sammy for four more. Another full delivery outside off, Akmal drills a lofted drive towards long-off who puts in a dive but can't hold on
Wahab Riaz to Umar Akmal, no run, yorker outside off, a hint of reverse. Akmal is beaten by the late movement
Wahab Riaz to Umar Akmal, FOUR, what a shot from Akmal. Full delivery on off, in the arc but Akmal times the pants off the drive. Whistles across to the cover boundary.
Wahab Riaz to Umar Akmal, 1 run, changes the pace, slower delivery outside off. Steered down to third man
Wahab Riaz to Delport, 1 run, awesome yorker. Follows the backing-away Delport and executes the toe-crusher to perfection. Off the pad, towards point
Tait to Delport, no run, short and wide, width on offer. Delport backs away and looks for a cut but misses
Tait to Delport, SIX, six. Delport pulls Tait for six over square leg. That was a quick delivery but Delport just uses the pace and finds adequate connection
Tait to Delport, 2 runs, short again, pulled all along the ground this time to deep square leg who puts in a boundary-saving dive
Tait to Delport, 1 run, turned to deep midwicket off the fullish delivery
Tait to Umar Akmal, 1 run, full and wide, skewed away towards point
Tait to Delport, 1 run, full and wide, belted down to mid-off for a run
Wahab Riaz to Delport, 1 run, a mis-timed drive, off the full delivery, finds mid-off
Wahab Riaz to Umar Akmal, 2 runs, superb shot gain. Did not get all of it though. Full and wide outside off, Akmal lofts the drive over cover
Wahab Riaz to Umar Akmal, 1 run, squeezed to deep point for one. Good over this so far. Akmal unable to get under the ball
Wahab Riaz to Delport, 2 runs, slower ball outside off, swatted away to long-off. Good fielding, but the pair get two
Wahab Riaz to Delport, 1 run, full and straight down leg, Delport drives to long-on
Wahab Riaz to Umar Akmal, 1 run, hit to deep midwicket. Not a bad over for Lahore despite no boundary. 8 off it.
Junaid Khan to Umar Akmal, 1 run, great ball. Full and wide, inside the tramline. Akmal guides the ball to deep point. Just one
Junaid Khan to Delport, FOUR, low full toss on leg, drilled to the long-on boundary. Great hit by Delport

Junaid Khan to Delport, OUT, slower bouncer on off, another slap with great timing but Delport picks out deep midwicket to perfection. Malan takes an easy catch. But Delport has played a blinder in tough conditions.
Junaid Khan to Umar Akmal, 1 run, full and wide, steered to deep point for another run
Junaid Khan to Bravo, 1 run, dropped, but he saved the boundary actually. Low full toss outside off, guided to short third man. Sammy gets a hand on it but can't hold on
Wicket: ['CS Delport c Malan b Junaid Khan 78 (61b 6x4 3x6) SR: 127.86']

Commentary: Junaid Khan to Umar Akmal, FOUR, driven over cover for a boundary for Akmal to get to his fifty. Great innings this from Akmal. 164 is what Lahore finish with.
